<subSubSection id="2FE250BDFFD0FFFFFF24FCAE19D7F80A" pageId="3" pageNumber="158" type="description">
<paragraph id="67470336FFD0FFFFFF24FCAE19D7F80A" blockId="3.[136,1452,842,1301]" pageId="3" pageNumber="158">
Ortega, in volume 6 of Quer’s 
<emphasis id="558CDF24FFD0FFFFFE4BFCAE1FBCFE7B" box="[487,665,842,868]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="158">Flora Española</emphasis>
(1784: 524) published the name 
<taxonomicName id="A0F878B5FFD0FFFFFBBEFCAE19D0FE7B" authorityName="Ortega" authorityYear="1784" box="[1042,1269,842,868]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Rubus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="3" pageNumber="158" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="non-spinosus">
<emphasis id="558CDF24FFD0FFFFFBBEFCAE19D0FE7B" box="[1042,1269,842,868]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="158">Rubus non-spinosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. In the index of the volume he lists the species in the Linnaean binary form. Obviously he considered these as the formal names of the plants. He added as author ‘ 
<emphasis id="558CDF24FFD0FFFFFE17FC771CD5FEB3" box="[443,496,915,940]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="158">Barr</emphasis>
.’, which refers to 
<bibRefCitation id="03697EC7FFD0FFFFFD15FC761E55FEB3" author="Barrelier, J." box="[697,880,914,940]" pageId="3" pageNumber="158" refId="ref4787" refString="Barrelier, J. (1714) Plantae per Galliam, Hispaniam et Italiam observatae iconibus aeneis exhibitae, ed. A. de Jussieu. Ganeau, Paris, 140 pp." type="book" year="1714">Barrelier (1714)</bibRefCitation>
. Because he also refers to p. 223 of his own volume the text about the taxon on that page is included in the protologue. He cites both 
<bibRefCitation id="03697EC7FFD0FFFFFB89FC5219F3FECF" author="Barrelier, J." box="[1061,1238,950,976]" pageId="3" pageNumber="158" refId="ref4787" refString="Barrelier, J. (1714) Plantae per Galliam, Hispaniam et Italiam observatae iconibus aeneis exhibitae, ed. A. de Jussieu. Ganeau, Paris, 140 pp." type="book" year="1714">Barrelier (1714</bibRefCitation>
: “Obs. 1373. Icon. 353”) and 
<bibRefCitation id="03697EC7FFD0FFFFFEACFC3E1F22FEEA" author="Tournefort, J. P." box="[256,519,986,1013]" pageId="3" pageNumber="158" refId="ref6376" refString="Tournefort, J. P. (1700) Institutiones rei herbariae 1. Typographia Regia, Parisiis, 697 pp. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 713" type="book" year="1700">Tournefort (1700: 614)</bibRefCitation>
, so that both are part of the protologue. No specimen of Barrelier could be found, only an image (
<bibRefCitation id="03697EC7FFD0FFFFFE94FC1A1CC4F907" author="Barrelier, J." box="[312,481,1022,1048]" pageId="3" pageNumber="158" refId="ref4787" refString="Barrelier, J. (1714) Plantae per Galliam, Hispaniam et Italiam observatae iconibus aeneis exhibitae, ed. A. de Jussieu. Ganeau, Paris, 140 pp." type="book" year="1714">Barrelier 1714</bibRefCitation>
: icon 353 [recte 395]) (
<figureCitation id="FFC31FB3FFD0FFFFFD40FC1A1E17F907" box="[748,818,1022,1048]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[136,229,1975,1997]" captionTargetBox="[597,990,1325,1950]" captionTargetId="figure-601@3.[597,990,1325,1950]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Lectotype of Rubus non-spinosus Ortega, [icon] “Rubus non spinosus, mai. fruct. nigr.” in Barrelier (1714: ic. 395)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5585402" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5585402/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="158">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
). On the other hand, in the herbarium of Tournefort is a good specimen of a thornless form of 
<taxonomicName id="A0F878B5FFD0FFFFFD96FBC71FECF923" baseAuthorityName="Van de Beek" baseAuthorityYear="2016" box="[570,713,1058,1084]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Rubus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="3" pageNumber="158" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ulmifolius">
<emphasis id="558CDF24FFD0FFFFFD96FBC71FECF923" box="[570,713,1058,1084]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="158">R. ulmifolius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<emphasis id="558CDF24FFD0FFFFFD75FBC61EAAF923" box="[729,911,1058,1084]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="158">Tournefort 6078</emphasis>
[at P-TRF]) (
<figureCitation id="FFC31FB3FFD0FFFFFB85FBC61949F923" box="[1065,1132,1058,1084]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="4.[136,229,1799,1821]" captionTargetBox="[341,1245,190,1775]" captionTargetId="figure-34@4.[341,1245,190,1775]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 3. Lectotype of Rubus fruticosus var.inermis Weston (P, Tournefort 6078, P-TRF).Image courtesy of the herbariumP,reproduced with permission." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5585406" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5585406/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="158">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
) but revised as 
<taxonomicName id="A0F878B5FFD0FFFFFAB2FBC71C29F97F" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Rubus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="3" pageNumber="158" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="fruticosus" variety="inermis">
<emphasis id="558CDF24FFD0FFFFFAB2FBC7180AF923" box="[1310,1327,1059,1084]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="158">R</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="558CDF24FFD0FFFFFA91FBC6188EF923" box="[1341,1451,1058,1084]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="158">fruticosus</emphasis>
var. 
<emphasis id="558CDF24FFD0FFFFFF14FBA31C29F97F" box="[184,268,1095,1120]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="158">inermis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(see this taxon below). However, this material was not cited in the protologue and neither can it be treated as original material used by Ortega to describe his species. We have not found any original material of this name in the herbaria consulted (e.g., BM, E, H, P, MA). Thus, the Barrelier’s illustration “ 
<taxonomicName id="A0F878B5FFD0FFFFFB90FB6A19A3F9B7" authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1753" box="[1084,1158,1166,1192]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Rubus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="3" pageNumber="158" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">Rubus</taxonomicName>
non spinosus, mai, fruct. nigr.” (1714: 395) cited by Ortega (without the abbreviations) in the protologue of 
<taxonomicName id="A0F878B5FFD0FFFFFBB1FB5719EAF9D3" authorityName="Ortega" authorityYear="1784" box="[1053,1231,1203,1228]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Rubus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="3" pageNumber="158" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="non-spinosus">
<emphasis id="558CDF24FFD0FFFFFBB1FB5719EAF9D3" box="[1053,1231,1203,1228]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="158">R. non-spinosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is designated as the 
<typeStatus id="B843BD94FFD0FFFFFF24FB321DCAF9EF" box="[136,239,1238,1264]" pageId="3" pageNumber="158">lectotype</typeStatus>
of the name. This drawing illustrates a complete plant, with leaves, flowers and fruits, without prickles, and matches with the traditional concept and current use of the name as a thornless form of 
<taxonomicName id="A0F878B5FFD0FFFFFBF0FB1F19CEF80B" baseAuthorityName="Van de Beek" baseAuthorityYear="2016" box="[1116,1259,1274,1300]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Rubus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="3" pageNumber="158" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ulmifolius">
<emphasis id="558CDF24FFD0FFFFFBF0FB1F19CEF80B" box="[1116,1259,1274,1300]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="158">R. ulmifolius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
